The paper deals with the problem of solar radiation prediction using novel wavelet recurrent neural networks. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and signal processing, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for solar radiation prediction. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as they are related to the use of machine learning techniques. cs.SD (Sound) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are less likely categories, but they are still relevant as the paper deals with signal processing and information theory concepts.
